<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-22T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-22T16:00:00-05:00" n="753" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d753">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Stettinius Mission/51:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-22T23:00:00+02:00">April
                                        22, 1944—11 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received April 22—8:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3341. Deles No. 27. From the Under Secretary. During discussions on
                                Saudi Arabia, Sir Maurice Peterson and Murray agreed British and
                                American economic authorities in Cairo should explore possibility of
                                joint Anglo-American goods subsidy program for Saudi Arabia being
                                guided in principle by standard of 50–50 participation so far as
                                this compatible with appropriate assignment of loading areas. If
                                Department perceives no objection I suggest Landis be authorized to
                                discuss the question in this sense with Jordan in reference to
                                Cairo’s 995, April 22 [<hi rend="italic">21</hi>], 2 p.m. repeating
                                to Department Cairo’s 44 same date to London.</p>
                            <p>Sent to Department. Repeated to Jidda and to Cairo for Landis.
                                [Stettinius.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>